{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Not to us, Lord, not to us, but to you all glory should be given, because of your trustworthy love and faithfulness.\n"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Why should the heathen nations ask,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Where is your God?",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Our God is in heaven, and he does whatever he wants."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Their idols are just things of silver and gold made by human hands."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They have mouths, but can't speak. They have eyes, but can't see."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They have ears, but can't hear. They have noses, but can't smell."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They have hands, but can't feel. They have feet, but can't walk. No sound comes from their throats. [^399]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Those who make idols become just like them, and so does everyone who trusts in them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Israel, trust in the Lord! He is the one who helps you and protects you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Descendants of Aaron, trust in the Lord! He is the one who helps you and protects you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Those who honor the Lord, trust in the Lord! He is the one who helps you and protects you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The Lord keeps us in mind and will be good to us. He will bless Israel, he will bless the descendants of Aaron."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The Lord will bless all those who worship him, whoever they are. [^400]"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "May the Lord be good to you, you and your children."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "May you be blessed by the Lord who made heaven and earth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The heavens belong to the Lord, but he has given the earth to humankind."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The dead do not praise the Lord, those who have gone down into the silence of the grave."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But we the living will always praise the Lord. Praise the Lord!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}